$Header$

Primitive directory lister.

Without options it has no sort, no stat(),
so it is quicker than ls, find or echo *.

Compile:
	make

Usage:
	dirlist
	dirlist DIR

        dirlist -rem0100000 | while read -r a; do eval a="\$'$a'"; ...

Future usage (not yet implemented):
	dirlist -0m040000 | dirlist -oz # list first dir
	dirlist -0m040000 | dirlist -0z | dirlist -z

About:
	See DESCRIPTION

-Tino
webmaster@scylla-charybdis.com
